Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FSliced-pieces-of-black-potatoes-1704205681-150x200.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-337295%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20black%20potatoes%20look%20like%20on%20the%20inside%20after%20being%20cut.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENutritional%20value%20of%20the%20black%20potatoes%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrincipal%20scientist%20at%20the%20Modipuram-based%20ICAR-Central%20Potato%20Research%20Institute%2C%20Regional%20Station%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fin.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fdr-satish-kumar-luthra-06a94248%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Dr%20Satish%20Kumar%20Luthra%3C%2Fa%3E%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CDark%20purple%20or%20red-skinned%20potatoes%20with%20purple%20or%20red%20flesh%20possess%20higher%20nutritional%20values%20than%20white-skinned%20potatoes.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Luthra%20is%20also%20credited%20with%20developing%20the%20%3Cem%3EKufri%20Neelkanth%3C%2Fem%3E%20potato%20variety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%2C%20purple%20often%20indicates%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F291624%2Fmillets-help-in-weight-loss-delicious-recipes-health-benefits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresence%20of%20nutrients%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20anthocyanins.%20Like%20other%20phytonutrients%2C%20your%20body%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20need%20them%20to%20function%2C%20but%20they%20do%20help%20protect%20your%20cells%20from%20damage%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20illness%20and%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20potatoes%20are%20probably%20rich%20in%20anthocyanins%2C%20imparting%20a%20deep%20purple%20colour.%20A%20class%20of%20flavonoids%2C%20anthocyanins%20are%20known%20to%20have%20several%20health%20benefits%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cftri.res.in%2FProfile%2F0_37803600_1534424669.pdf%5C%22%3E%20Dr%20Pradeep%20Singh%20Negi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chief%20Scientist%2C%20Fruit%20and%20Vegetable%20Technology%20Department%20at%20Mysore-based%20CSIR-Central%20Food%20Technological%20Research%20Institute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20hues%20from%20blue%20to%20red%2C%20anthocyanins%20are%20water-soluble%20and%20are%20used%20as%20food%20colourant%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20all%20potato%20varieties%20impact%20blood%20sugar%20levels%20because%20of%20their%20carbohydrate%20content%2C%20black%20potatoes%20may%20exert%20less%20of%20an%20effect%20than%20other%20types%20due%20to%20their%20high%20concentration%20of%20polyphenol%20plant%20compounds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20anthocyanins%2C%20they%20have%202-3%20times%20the%20total%20antioxidants%20of%20a%20typical%20white%20potato%2C%20which%20is%20loaded%20with%20potassium%2C%20magnesium%2C%20vitamin%20C%2C%20and%20fibre.%20Fruits%20such%20as%20jamun%2C%20blueberries%2C%20and%20blackberries%20are%20rich%20in%20anthocyanins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20glycemic%20index%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fnutrition%2Fpurple-potatoes%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520glycemic%2520index%2520(GI)%2520is%2CGI%2520of%252093%2520(%25205%2520).%5C%22%3E(GI)%20measures%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20food%20raises%20your%20blood%20sugar.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20ranges%20from%200%20to%20100%2C%20and%20a%20GI%20greater%20than%2070%20is%20considered%20high.%20A%20comparison%20study%20in%20humans%20found%20that%20black%20potatoes%20have%20a%20GI%20of%2077%2C%20yellow%20potatoes%20have%20a%20GI%20of%2081%2C%20and%20white%20potatoes%20have%20a%20GI%20of%2093.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20720px)%20100vw%2C%20720px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FBlack-potatoes-1704205878.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%